9. Remarks

· Hybrid Optimization: The inclusion of gradient descent on continuous parameters (with a decaying step size) ensures that the constants converge to optimal values for each tree structure, as proved in Theorem 1.1.
· Diversity: The injection mechanism, combined with the dynamic threshold \delta(t), guarantees a lower bound on population entropy (Theorem 3.4) and prevents premature convergence.
· Symmetry Reduction: The grammar already encodes physical symmetries, drastically reducing the effective search space and justifying the use of evolutionary search on this structured manifold (Lemma 4.1).
· Convergence: The Markov chain irreducibility (Lemma 3.2) and elitist selection (modified NSGA‑II) guarantee almost‑sure convergence to the global Pareto front (Theorem 3.1). The expected hitting time is bounded (Theorem 3.3).

